A police officer was shot and wounded early Saturday morning after responding to a burglary call, authorities have revealed. 

The unnamed man, who works for the Minneapolis Police Department, was gunned down while standing outside his patrol car at around 5am, with authorities suggesting he was targeted.

Andrew Neal, 43, was reportedly taken into custody by police on Saturday afternoon in connection with the shooting. He is believed to have a long criminal history. 

